Southern Turkish Businesses See Fewer Tourists on Syria Unrest, Dunya Says

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-03-29T05:20:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-29/southern-turkish-businesses-brace-for-syria-unrest-dunya-says.html
Businessmen in the southern Turkish
city of Antakya say unrest in neighboring  Syria  has already
reduced the number of tourists crossing into the country and is
likely to impact trade, Dunya newspaper said.  Manufacturers and tourism companies are bracing for a
turndown in business, the newspaper reported, citing Yahya Kemal
Nalcabasmaz, head of the Association of Hatat Industrialists and
Executives.  Tourists are already wary of making the journey over the
border to Aleppo, Dunya said, citing Aykut Ozbugday, head of the
Hatay Young Executives Association.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
